# Test Cube for Physics Testing
# Unit cube centered at origin with normals, texture coordinates, and colored materials
# Material assignments pre-compensate for orientMeshYUpToZUp + flipMeshWinding:
# Y-up Top -> Final Back (Red), Y-up Bottom -> Final Front (Green)
# Y-up Front -> Final Bottom (Blue), Y-up Back -> Final Top (Yellow)
# Y-up Left -> Final Left (Cyan), Y-up Right -> Final Right (Magenta)

mtllib TestCube.mtl

# Vertices
v -0.5 -0.5 -0.5
v  0.5 -0.5 -0.5
v  0.5  0.5 -0.5
v -0.5  0.5 -0.5
v -0.5 -0.5  0.5
v  0.5 -0.5  0.5
v  0.5  0.5  0.5
v -0.5  0.5  0.5

# Normals (Y-up: Z=depth, Y=up, X=right)
vn 0.0  0.0 -1.0    # Back: -Z -> becomes Top final
vn 0.0  0.0  1.0    # Front: +Z -> becomes Bottom final
vn 0.0 -1.0  0.0    # Bottom: -Y -> becomes Front final
vn 0.0  1.0  0.0    # Top: +Y -> becomes Back final
vn -1.0  0.0  0.0   # Left: -X
vn 1.0  0.0  0.0    # Right: +X

# Texture coordinates
vt 0.0 0.0
vt 1.0 0.0
vt 1.0 1.0
vt 0.0 1.0

# Back face (z = -0.5) in Y-up -> Top face final -> assign Yellow
usemtl back_yellow
f 1/1/1 2/2/1 3/3/1 4/4/1
# Front face (z = 0.5) in Y-up -> Bottom face final -> assign Blue
usemtl front_blue
f 5/1/2 6/2/2 7/3/2 8/4/2
# Bottom face (y = -0.5) in Y-up -> Front face final -> assign Green
usemtl bottom_green
f 1/1/3 5/2/3 6/3/3 2/4/3
# Top face (y = 0.5) in Y-up -> Back face final -> assign Red
usemtl top_red
f 4/1/4 8/2/4 7/3/4 3/4/4
# Left face (x = -0.5) - Cyan
usemtl left_cyan
f 1/1/5 4/4/5 8/3/5 5/2/5
# Right face (x = 0.5) - Magenta
usemtl right_magenta
f 2/1/6 3/4/6 7/3/6 6/2/6
